# Auto Restart After Changes

- After completing meaningful backend or frontend changes, restart the relevant running service(s) when it is safe to do so.
- Prefer restarting the app directly instead of asking the user to do it manually.
- After restart, verify the service is up and report the visible effect or any startup errors.
- If multiple services are involved, restart the minimum set needed to show the new behavior.
- Do not restart if doing so would clearly risk data loss or interrupt a user-critical long-running operation.
- If a restart fails, fix the issue or explain the blocker and continue from there.
